<paragraph blockId="3.[313,1269,978,1608]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2415">
<emphasis box="[353,706,1393,1417]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2415">
Ecology. 
<taxonomicName authority="Bellan &amp; Dauvin &amp; Laubier, 2003" authorityName="Bellan &amp; Dauvin &amp; Laubier" authorityYear="2003" box="[476,706,1393,1417]" class="Polychaeta" family="Spionidae" genus="Lindaspio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spionida" pageId="3" pageNumber="2415" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="sebastiena" status="n. sp.">Lindaspio sebastiena</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[714,776,1393,1416]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2415" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
was collected in the N’Kossa (
<collectingCountry name="Republic of the Congo" pageId="3" pageNumber="2415">Republic of Congo</collectingCountry>
) oil field. Sediment is a muddy (30% silt) coarse sand (41% sand) containing a large amount of organic carbon (2.4%), barium (5210 ppm) and hydrocarbons (4680 ppm). These three pollutants come from the oil-field drilling. More important species of the community are, with 
